ju)|Drawa]]''' (Polish) |- | [[Drin (river)|Drin]] | {{flagicon|ALB}} {{flagicon|KOS}} {{flagicon|MKD}} | '''Drilon''' (Latin),<ref>{{cite web |url=https://pleiades.stoa.org/places/481815 |title=Places: 481815 (Drilon (river)) |author=Wilkes, J. |accessdate=July 18, 2018|publisher=Pleiades}}</ref> '''Drim''' - ''[[:mk:Дрим|Дрим]]'' (Macedonian, Serbian), '''[[:it:Drin|Drin]]''' (French, German, Italian, Turkish), '''[[:sq:Lumi i Drinit|Drini]]''' (Albanian) |- | [[Drina]] | {{flagicon|MNE}} {{flagicon|SRB}} {{flagicon|BIH}} | '''Dreinos''' - ''Δρεινος'' (Ancient Greek), '''[[:bs:Drina|Drina]]''' (Bosnian, Albanian, Hungarian, Italian, etc.), '''Drina''' - ''[[:sr:Дрина|Дрина]]'' (Serbian, Macedonian), '''Drinos''' - ''[[:el:Δρίνος|Δρινος]]'' (Greek), '''Drinus''' (Latin), <!-- This appears to be a Serbian nick name, meaning "Green River; any refs for the following?: '''Zelenika''' (Old ancient Slavic name : "green river" - same meanings as Drina in Illyrrian )--> |- | [[Drôme (river)|Drôme]] | {{flagicon|FRA}} | '''[[:oc:Droma (riu)|Droma]]''' (Occitan, Breton, Catalan, Early Modern Spanish), '''[[:fr:Drôme|Drôme]]''' (French) |- | [[Drut River|Drut]] | {{flagicon|BLR}} | '''[[:fr:Drout|Drout]]''' (French), '''[[:cz:Druc|Druc]]''' (Czech), '''Drut’''' - ''[[:ru:Друть|Друть]]'' (Russian, Ukrainian), '''Druts''' or '''Druć''' - ''[[:be:Друць|Друць]]'' (Belarusian) |- | [[Drwęca]] | {{flagicon|POL}} | '''[[:de:Drwęca|Drewenz]]''' (German), '''[[:lt:Druvinčia|Druvinčia]]''' (Lithuanian), '''[[:lv:Drvenca|Drvenca]]''' (Latvian), '''Drventsa''' - ''[[:uk: Дрвенца|Дрвенца]]'' (Ukrainian), '''[[:pl:Drwęca|Drwęca]]''' (Polish) |- | [[Dunajec]] | {{flagicon|POL}} {{flagicon|SVK}} | '''[[:de:Dunajec|Dohnst]]''' (German; archaic), '''[[:pl:Dunajec|Dunajec]]''' (Polish, Slovak), '''[[:de:Dunajec|Dunajez]]''' or '''Dunajetz''' (German) |- | [[Durance]] | {{flagicon|FRA}} | '''Drouentia''' - ''Δrουεντια'' (Ancient Greek),<ref>[[Strabo]], ca. 10 AD, [http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/ho