a]] | {{flagicon|RUS}} | '''Ĭov''' - ''[[:ru:Мокша (река)|Йов]]'' (locally in [[Moksha language|Moksha]]), '''Măkshǎ''' - ''[[:cv:Мăкшă (юханшыв)|Мăкшă]]'' ([[Chuvash language|Chuvash]]), '''Moksha''' - ''[[:mdf:Мокша (ляй)|Мокша]]'' (Moksha, Russian), '''Moksho''' - [[:mhr:Мокшо (эҥер)|Мокшо]]'' ([[Mari language|Mari]]), '''Mükşı''' - ''[[:tt:Мукшы (елга)|Мукшы]]'' (Tatar) |- | [[Moldova River|Moldova]] | {{flagicon|ROM}} | '''[[:de:Moldova (Fluss)|Moldau]]''' (German), '''[[:it:Moldavia (fiume)|Moldavia]]''' (Italian, Portuguese, Spanish), '''[[:pl:Mołdawa (rzeka)|Mołdawa]]''' (Polish), '''[[:ro:Râul Moldova|Moldova]]''' (Romanian, French), '''Mulduha''' and '''Mulduva''' (16th-century Romanian)<ref>Dragoş Moldovanu, [http://www.diacronia.ro/ro/indexing/details/A1415/pdf Etimologia Hidronimului Moldova], Editura Academiei 1981-82 (in Romanian)<br>Andrei Brezianu, Vlad Spânu, [https://books.google.com/books?id=bgcCelRuTboC&pg=PA240#v=onepage&q&f=false The A to Z of Moldova], Scarecrow Press, 2010, p. 240</ref> |- | [[Molochna River|Molochna]] | {{flagicon|UKR}} | '''Gerros''' - ''Γέρρος'' (Ancient Greek),<ref>[https://pleiades.stoa.org/places/226603 Gerros (river)] at pleaiades.stoa.org</ref> '''Gerrus''' (Latin), '''Molochna''' - ''[[:uk: Молочна|Молочна]] (Ukrainian), '''Molochnaya''' - [[:ru:Молочная (река)|Молочная]]'' (Russian), '''[[:fr:Molotchna| Molotchna]]''' (French),'''[[:de:Molotschna| Molotschna]]''' (German), '''Tokmachka''' - ''[[:ru:Молочная (река)|Токмачка]]'' (Ukrainian; upper part) |- | [[Mondego River|Mondego]] | {{flagicon|POR}} | '''[[:pt:Rio Mondego|Mondego]]''' (Portuguese, Asturian, Galician, Spanish), '''Mundas''' (Latin)<ref name=rpar>Brian Campbell, [https://books.google.com/books?id=oeYiISgcJQIC Rivers and the Power of Ancient Rome], Appendix 2: Navigable Rivers according to Ancient Authors, pp 405-10, UNC Press Books, 2012</ref>, '''[[:mwl:Riu Mundego|Mundego]]''' ([[Mirandese language|Mirandese]])
