ian, German, Turkmen), '''Wołga''' (Polish, Silesian) |- | [[Volkhov River|Volkhov]] | {{flagicon|RUS}} | '''Olhav''' (Veps), '''Olhava''' (Ingrian), '''Olhavanjoki''' (Finnish), '''Volhova''' (Latvian), '''Volhovi jõgi''' (Estonian), '''Vóljov''' (Spanish), '''Volkhov''' - ''Во́лхов'' (Russian), '''Wolchow''' (German), '''Wołchow''' (Polish) |- | [[Vuoksi River|Vuoksi]] | {{flagicon|RUS}} {{flagicon|FIN}} | '''Vuoksa''' (Norwegian), '''Vuoksa''' - ''Вуокса'' (Russian), '''Vuoksen''' (Swedish), '''Vuoksi''' (Finnish, French, German) |- | [[Vyatka River|Vyatka]] | {{flagicon|RUS}} | '''Noqrat''' - ''Нократ'' (Tatar), '''Nuhrat Atăl''' - ''Нухрат Атăл'' (Chuvash), '''Vatka''' - ''Ватка'' (Mari, Udmurt), '''Viatca''' (Latin), '''Viatka''' (French, Spanish), '''Viče''' - ''Виче'' (Mari), '''Vjatka''' (Dutch, Italian), '''Vyatka''' - ''Вя́тка'' (Russian), '''Wiatka''' (Polish), '''Wjatka''' (German) |- | [[Vychegda]] | {{flagicon|RUS}} | '''Ežva''' - ''Эжва'' (Komi), '''Vychegda''' - ''Вычегда'' (Russian), '''Vytchegda''' (French), '''Wytschegda''' (German) |}
